  <main id="main-content">
    <section id="why-learn" aria-labelledby="why-learn-heading">
      <h2 id="why-learn-heading">Why Learn to Code?</h2>
      <p>Coding empowers you with problem-solving skills and opens career paths in technology, web development, data science, AI, and more.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="start" aria-labelledby="start-heading">
      <h2 id="start-heading">Getting Started</h2>
      <article>
        <h3>Pick Your First Language</h3>
        <p>Begin with beginner-friendly languages such as Python or JavaScript, known for their readability and strong community support.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Set Achievable Goals</h3>
        <p>Define what you want to build; either websites, scripts to automate tasks, or mobile apps, and focus your learning path around that goal.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Practice Consistently</h3>
        <p>Dedicate regular time; at least 20 to 30 minutes per day, to building and improving your coding skills through hands-on practice.</p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section id="projects" aria-labelledby="projects-heading">
      <h2 id="projects-heading">Beginner Project Ideas</h2>
      <article>
        <h3>Personal Portfolio Website</h3>
        <figure>
          <img src="portfolio.jpg" alt="Screenshot of a personal portfolio website page">
          <figcaption>Showcase your projects and introduce yourself.</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <p>Create a simple web page featuring your bio, skills, and coding projects using HTML and CSS.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Console Calculator</h3>
        <p>Build and test a basic calculator script using your chosen language to practice handling input, output, and arithmetic logic.</p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <details id="faq">
      <summary>Frequently Asked Questions</summary>
      <p><strong>How long does it take to learn coding?</strong><br>It depends on consistency; but with daily practice, beginners often start building simple projects within a few weeks.</p>
      <p><strong>Do I need a degree?</strong><br>No. Many coders succeed through self-learning, practice, and real-world projects shared online.</p>
      <p><strong>What if I don't have a tech background?</strong><br>Still ok, many have learned how to code from the beginning without a prior background.</p>
    </details>
  </main>

